f   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":40,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth was born in 1415, in Northwick, Worcestershire, England. She married Edmund Childe in 1431, in Worcester, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1522, in Northwick, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 107."},"et":{"1415–1522":"1415–1522","1412–1459":"1412–1459","1432–1520":"1432–1520","1434–1511":"1434–1511","1440–1522":"1440–1522","1415":"1415","1459":"1459","1434":"1434","1511":"1511","1522":"1522","1412":"1412","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1520":"1520","1431":"1431","1440":"1440","Worcester, Worcestershire, , England":"Worcester, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northwick, Worcester, England":"Northwick, Worcestershire, England","Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worcester, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northwick, Worcestershire, England":"Northwick, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northwick, Worchester, England":"Northwick, Worcester